    "Thus, positive selection was significantly associated with orthogroup type (CORE vs random; chi-sq., p < 0.001; Additional file 2: Fig.",
    "Together, these results suggest orthogroups that are consistently differentially expressed across Theobroma spp.",
    "following pathogen challenge are evolving under positive selection.",
    "DiscussionPlant pathogens responsible for extensive annual yield loss in crop species, a problem that is likely to become worse due to climate change.",
    "Through breeding, humans have sought to mitigate the damage these pathogens cause by harnessing natural variation in resistance/susceptibility."
